@Patrick J. - When teaching about molting in invertebrates, I found students had difficulty recalling the scientific term for molting, which is "ecdysis." 

I always tried to find way to help my students remember things, so I asked them if they knew what an ecdysiast was. Usually none of them knew, so when I told them, after the shock that their professor would talk about such things in class wore off, almost all of them remembered the term. 

It was always one of my more effective mnemonic devices.

